age</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(4/10/02 4:29:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=370.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Magician's best partner for duo?  </span><hr size=1> I realize that mages probably get their best exp in an AE group, but when they aren't AEing or soloing or grouping, what do they do?   <br>
<br>
DO mages ever duo with another class for exp?  As a shaman I've thrived on the duo game.  I take any melee class (even rogue), buff them to the gills, and we gain mad exp as a duo.  With a monk, I can do FGs in solb, all of em.  I've done minor dragons in WW with a paladin partner, and a ranger partner.  <br>
<br>
But mages . . . I've duoed with them before . . and it worked out ok.  But recently something has changed to make me take another look at the mage class for duo possibilities.  <br>
<br>
That change is modrod2.  No, I don't want your mod rods, sheesh.  I wanna Torpor you.  *mage's eyes light up*  <br>
With me being more than capable of keeping a mage in continuous Torpor (without reducing my own mana over time), can you think of possibilities with modrod2?  <br>
<br>
To my calculations, if a mage is kept in continuous Torpor, that's 300 dmg/tic healing power, 300 dmg from modrod2, and 200 mana gain from three charges.  Assuming continuous mod rodding, that Torpor heals 1200 hps total, and that the mage can make new mod rods while healing . . . . I come up with about 75 mana/tic I can pump into a mage . . . at no appreciable loss to my own mana pool.  <br>
<br>
I did this last night in an akheva group.  The mage was 60 and loved to modrod . . . I kept her in Torpor more often than not, in addition to slowing and rooting mobs that were pulled.  The monk kept a continuous stream of mobs incoming and the mage used AE spells mostly I think.  Stuff died incredibly fast . . . I think the mage was doing at least half the total group damage simply cause she had the mana to do so.  <br>
<br>
I have the AA skill Cannibalization, which I can use every 3 minutes to drop 1924hps and gain 1100 mana.  This recharges the old battery if I get low . . . basically I have more mana than I know what to do with most times.  I can transfer this to a mage at a ratio greater than 1:1, and mages frankly do much better and faster damage than I am capable of doing.  My nukes are pathetic and easily resisted, my dots take too long.  Magician spell damage however, is uber.   <br>
<br>
Any of you mages out there with modrod2 have similar experiences?  Based on my tale o' Torpor, would a shaman like myself make the best Magician duo partner?  <br>
<br>
Landragoran Heronwing<br>
Oracle of Justice<br>
Riders of the Apocalypse<br>
Lanys<br>
<br>
