<br>
Dmg shield &gt; slow.  Dmg shield &gt; mez.<br>
<br>
I'd rather have a couple mobs beating on epic and just CHing him than fighting single slowed mobs =p.  <br>
<br>
I have a 60 mage and a 60 cleric duo, and it works VERY well.  Can hold disco, guardian, exit, gang camps in seb with ease, krup camps are a bit tougher as no solo pulls.  Can do udogs in velks, most zones in luclin... and decent xp.  <br>
<br>
Constant pulls but the pet taking xp thing really hurts =/  Ya i know i could outdamage it with constant nukes, but BoB + CHs while just keeping mobs on pet is more effecient from my experiences.  <br>
<br>
<br>
However, the best exp i have run around so far is just adding a monk or other melee to the group.  Head to the deep or somewhere decently tough, and make sure you get someone that knows how to play with pet agro.  Been able to get killer xp in these types of trios.  <br>
<br>
(yes i keep cleric grouped at all times). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1275<br> <font color=#333333>(4/10/02 5:45:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=370.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magician's best partner for duo?  </span><hr size=1> I do not know whether it was objective correct or not, but it seemed to me that my neighbor shaman prefered to solo rather than partner with me.  That is, while he brought a lot to me, maybe I did not bring enough to him.  Or maybe he was in a bad mood.<br>
<br>
Generally, I partner well enough with nearly any caster or priest.  Healers can buff <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and keep him alive, allowing me to greatly ramp up the rate of pulls.  As clerics cannot really solo alone, they are more willing partners than other classes that can solo.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Necromancer</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> works well, a second pet, and heals and dots.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Enchanter</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has not yet been satisfying, although a much younger one helps and does not take as large a share of experience.<br>
<br>
Melees generally do not work out well, as there is little I can do to support them.  There is a nice <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ranger</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> tactic that involved alternating a single whack with a big slow weapon with arrows at a distance that works well with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but it is a lot of work for the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ranger</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
One consideration when partnering is to make sure the experience flows well.  This includes outdamaging the pet, and increasing the kills per hour.  Having a much junior partner also works well.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
